  "description": "Hardy annual or short-lived perennial from Amaranthaceae, native to western North America. Produces spinach-like leaves in juvenile phase; bolts to produce dense fruiting spikes bearing small red berries. Dual-harvest crop: early leaves, then post-bolting berries. Self-seeds aggressively; hardy to USDA zone 2.",
  "name": "Chenopodium capitatum",
